\subsubsection{Minor Illusions}
\index{illusions!minor}

\begin{description}

\item[Coloured Lights] One or more globes of coloured light are
created by the caster for [D - 4] minutes.  These may be tossed
through the air, as long as they remain with ten feet of the caster.
They do not shed light on their surroundings.

\item[Graffiti]
A faintly glowing mark appears on the surface of an object.  With
practise the caster can ``write'', or draw simple pictures.  The
image will immediately start to fade, and disappear within [D + 5]
minutes.

\item[Noise]
A ``white'' noise emanates from any point within 20 feet of the
caster.  While this may startle animals, sentients will normally
disregard the sound almost immediately.

\item[Perfume]
A pleasant (or slightly unpleasant) scent may be imparted.  Observers
will not notice any particular odour, just that something smells nice
(or bad).  If they concentrate on the scent they will realise
immediately that it is an illusion.
